Interface EventListener<E,S,D>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the parameterized event type.
    S - the parameterized type of the event source.
    D - the parameterized type of the event data.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SvgDots.SvgDotsListener, Videojs.VideojsListener

    public interface EventListener<E,S,D>
extends Serializable
    Interface shared by all listeners handled in an EventManager object.
    Author:
    GeoSoft

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void on(E event, S source, D data)
      Called in response to a EventManager.callListeners(String, S, T) call if the present listener is registered to listen for the given event.

    • Method Detail

      • on

        void on(E event,
      S source,
      D data)
        Called in response to a EventManager.callListeners(String, S, T) call if the present listener is registered to listen for the given event.
        Parameters:
        event - The event object fired.
        source - The source the event (as defined by caller).
        data - Additional data (as defined by caller).
